    "name": "Postoperative Fever",
    "system": "surgical",
    "agePeak_months": [],
    "note": "Fever is common after surgery. Must be systematically investigated to distinguish benign causes (atelectasis, inflammatory response) from life-threatening complications (infection, anastomotic leak, PE). The 5 Ws mnemonic: Wind (atelectasis), Water (UTI), Wound (SSI), Walking (DVT/PE), Wonder (drug-related).",
    "prevalenceWeight": 0.25,
    "syndromeTags": ["postoperative_complication", "fever_postop", "nosocomial_infection"],

